Installing xml2sql (UNIX / Linux)
---------------------------------

xml2sql provides GNU autoconf/automake configure script.

    $ ./configure
    $ make
    # make install

You shoud use "gmake" instead of "make" if you are using
FreeBSD or Solaris.

By default, executable will be installed to /usr/local/bin.
You could change the installation directory by giving --prefix
option to configure.

For more help with configure script, type
    $ ./configure --help


Installing xml2sql (Windows)
----------------------------

You can compile xml2sql using Microsoft Visual C++ .NET.

xml2sql requires expat, zlib, and GNU getopt.

  1. Install Platform SDK from Microsoft Web Site.
  2. Make sure INCLUDE and LIB environment variables contain expat and zlib.
  3. Copy getopt.c, getopt.h, and getopt1.c into the source directory.
  4. Invoke nmake.exe.
       > nmake -f win/Makefile

